  "subject": "UI and Backend changes to support creation of Control Loop using a Loop Template. Create Loop from the available Loop templates. Configuration Policy moodal to support a Dropdown for choosing the Policy variant if a Microservice(loop element model) has more than one associated Policy models. Dropdown uses the acronym field to display as label and value as policy model type. Rewrite Configuration Policy Modal to support Single as well as Multiple policies in a list. This changes also adds policy naming using user defined name (if name tag exists) and using acronym Fixes a bug in PolicyModelsService update API and Dictionary API.",
  "commit_message": "UI and Backend changes to support creation of Control Loop using a Loop Template.\nCreate Loop from the available Loop templates.\nConfiguration Policy moodal to support a Dropdown for choosing the Policy variant if a Microservice(loop element model) has more than one associated Policy models.\nDropdown uses the acronym field to display as label and value as policy model type.\nRewrite Configuration Policy Modal to support Single as well as Multiple policies in a list.\nThis changes also adds policy naming using user defined name (if name tag exists) and using acronym\nFixes a bug in PolicyModelsService update API and Dictionary API.\n\nIssue-ID: CLAMP-587\nChange-Id: Ie94a94bad955142a4904fe21ff7358bcb7223f6e\nSigned-off-by: Ashwin Sharma <ashwin.shyam.sharma@att.com>\n",
